article.description: Tim Derksen tipped in a Devin Watson miss with 10 seconds left, then added a pair of free throws to give San Francisco a 96-93 overtime win over Coppin State Friday night.
article.headline: Derksen rescues San Francisco in OT, tops Coppin State 96-93
article.linkText: Derksen rescues San Francisco in OT, tops Coppin State 96-93
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Tim Derksen tipped in a Devin Watson miss with 10 seconds left, then added a pair of free throws to give San Francisco a 96-93 overtime win over Coppin State Friday night. James Sylvester hit a 3-pointer with 2:11 left in overtime to put Coppin State up 93-90, but the Eagles did not score again. Watson sank two free throws with 43 seconds left to pull the Dons within one, 93-92, but missed a layup with 12 seconds left. Derksen came down with the rebound and his putback gave San Francisco the lead. Derksen stole the ball from Joshua Treadway with a second left to seal the win. Sylvester hit two free throws with 4 seconds left in regulation to force overtime. Watson finished with 31 points and Derksen 23 to lead San Francisco (6-4). Terry Harris Jr. scored 27 points to lead Coppin State (2-9).
